Episodes.Title: The New Guy
Episodes.Plot: After Myka leaves the warehouse, Pete gets a new partner: ATF agent Steven Jinks, who has a gift for sensing when someone is lying. Pete and Steven take on a new case in Denver, while Artie, Claudia, and Leena deal with a deadly pair of statues at Warehouse 13.
Episodes.GuestStars: Aaron Ashmore, Ashley Williams, Jaime Murray, Mark Robinson

Episodes.Title: Trials
Episodes.Plot: While Pete and Myka go after someone using an artifact to induce Alzheimer's, Claudia goes on her first case as a full agent with Steve to track down Typhoid Mary's knife.

Episodes.Title: Love Sick
Episodes.Plot: While Artie and Claudia meet with Vanessa Calder and Hugo Miller to investigate a computer virus that transforms people into clay, Myka and Pete wake up naked in bed and try to find a missing Steve.
Episodes.GuestStars: Aaron Ashmore, Sasha Roiz, Ashley Williams, Rene Auberjonois, Lindsay Wagner, Max Morrow

Episodes.Title: Queen for a Day
Episodes.Plot: While Claudia and Steve attempt to infiltrate a Civil War reenactment to recover U.S. Grant's flask, Pete and Myka must deal with Pete's ex-wife... who has been stung by an artifact bee that has turned her into a human queen bee.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jeri Ryan, Aaron Ashmore, Anthony Lemke

Episodes.Plot: Pete, Myka and H.G. Wells track Joshua's Trumpet, an artifact that has eluded three generations of Warehouse agents, which now may pose a threat to a packed baseball stadium.
Episodes.GuestStars: Gareth David-Lloyd, Jaime Murray, Chad Connell

Episodes.Title: Don't Hate the Player
Episodes.Plot: Fargo becomes trapped in a video game inspired by Warehouse 13 and requires help from Pete, Claudia and Myka. Meanwhile, Stukowski recruits Artie and Steve to help with a case, and catches them stealing an artifact.
Episodes.GuestStars: Neil Grayston, Sasha Roiz, Steven Yeun, Ashley Williams, Aaron Ashmore

Episodes.Title: Past Imperfect
Episodes.Plot: While in Denver, Myka picks up the trail of the counterfeiter who killed her former partner, Sam Martino. Meanwhile, Artie, Claudia, and Steve interrogate a dog that witnessed the theft of an artifact.

Episodes.Title: The 40th Floor
Episodes.Plot: Sally Stukowski and her partner make their move, attacking the Regents and using an artifact to trap them in a building and bring it down around them.
Episodes.GuestStars: Aaron Ashmore, Faran Tahir, Kate Mulgrew, Ashley Williams, Sasha Roiz, CCH Pounder, Paula Boudreau, Andrew Jackson

Episodes.Title: Shadows
Episodes.Plot: While Pete and his mother Jane try to determine the origins of their mysterious opponents, Myka and Claudia travel to Portland to stop a girl who can apparently vaporize anyone she hates with blasts of radiation.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kate Mulgrew, Anthony Michael Hall, Alessandra Torresani, Sasha Roiz, CCH Pounder, Emily Andrews

Episodes.Title: Insatiable
Episodes.Plot: Myka and Pete deal with a plague of zombies in Ithaca, while Claudia deals with a new romance, a prophecy of death, and a rejection from a friend.
Episodes.GuestStars: Aaron Ashmore, Sasha Roiz, Johnny Pacar, Jenny Raven

Episodes.Title: Emily Lake (1)
Episodes.Plot: As Sykes begins his end game, the agents discover that Helena is still alive... and teaching high school literature. Meanwhile, Jane reveals the full extent of her plan but one agent will lose their life carrying it out.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kate Mulgrew, Aaron Ashmore, Jaime Murray, Faran Tahir, Sasha Roiz, Anthony Michael Hall, Max Morrow

Episodes.Title: Stand (2)
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka race to stop Sykes from using his own cache of artifacts to destroy them and the Warehouse.
Episodes.GuestStars: Anthony Michael Hall, Aaron Ashmore, Kate Mulgrew, Erick Avari, Sasha Roiz, Jaime Murray, CCH Pounder, Max Morrow

Episodes.Title: The Greatest Gift
Episodes.Plot: Holiday Special: Pete is hit in the head by an artifact and wakes up to a life where he was never born. Pete must hunt down and persuade the Warehouse team (none of whom recognize him) to go on this life or death mission with him to vanquish a long dead nemesis from the past to get everyone?s lives back.
Episodes.GuestStars: Roger Rees, Charles Malik Whitfield, Susan Hogan, CCH Pounder, Skyler Wexler
